<s:slide id="jcr" status="ready">
<s:title>JCR - Java Content Repository API</s:title>
<s:content>
<p>
<ol>
  <li>Specifies a standard API to access content repositories in Java 2 independently of implementation</li>
  <li>Very similar to WebDAV, whereas WebDAV is a protocol</li>
  <li>David Nuescheler (Day Software): Java Specification Request</li>
  <li>JCR 1.0: <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170">JSR-170</a></li>
  <li>JCR 2.0: <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=283">JSR-283</a></li>
</ol>
</p>
</s:content>
</s:slide>

